{
  "stem": "2067.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 14.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the plan ripened to escape.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we make use of the address that Eddie, Dottie's father, had left behind with, with her parents, namely a smuggler who lived in the town of Tilburg, in southeastern Holland.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He had taken-- he had a so-called organization of smugglers that took young people from Holland through Belgium, Paris, occupied and non-occupied France, to Lyon, up to Lyon.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in Lyon, we had heard already rumors that there was a Dutch representation.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they helped those people, those refugees, to get into Switzerland.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We started corresponding and informing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I informed Dottie that we thought we would not be able to stay for the duration of the war in, in that attic.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "First of all, we, we felt that we couldn't, we couldn't stand it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And secondly, the danger was too high.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All that was not written like I'm telling it now.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was written in very carefully-chosen words that, that she understood, but anyone who would read it would, would, would think this is gibberish, and what does it mean?",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "These guys don't even speak a normal language.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we understood each other.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had learned to write this kind of secret language.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She agreed.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She also felt that she could not stay for any length of time because for other reasons, one of the reasons being that the two boys went to school.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The wife went-- left the house in the morning to search for food, getting on her bicycle and traveling sometimes 50 miles to, to get food.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And Dottie was there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And sometimes, he would stay home from business and made advances to her, which she was lucky to fight off.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
